when I tried to run python from its file from the terminal, I got the below error:
ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'Flask'

to show where Flash has been installed, do:
=> pip show flask

Check the link below for instructions:
https://flask.palletsprojects.com/en/1.1.x/installation/#virtual-environments

To install the virtual environment on Linux, do:
=> sudo apt-get install python-virtualenv

To activiate the environment, do:
=> . venv/bin/activate

Now try to re-install the Flask packages again:

To doube check if pip is installed:
=> pip -V

To check pip packages list:
=> pip list

To uninstall a specific pip package:
=> pip uninstall package-name

You can run your Python file from the terminal (being on the right directory folder) in 2 ways:
=> python3 + file pathway
or
=> export FLASK_APP=file-name
=> export FLASK_ENV=development
=> flask run

e.g.
=> export FLASK_APP=run.py
=> export FLASK_ENV=development
=> flask run

To install pip3
=> pip3 install flask

To install flask-login
=> pip3 install flask-login

To set up python virtual env.
python3.8 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate
pip3 install pip --upgrade
pip3 install flask
pip3 install flask-SQLAlchemy (if produces error => /bin/python3: can't find '**main**' module in), then try the method below:
pip3 install flask-SQLAlchemy==3.0.3
pip3 install flask_wtf flask_bootstrap email_validator install

# flask_sqlalchemy

To install SQLite on ubuntu follow:
https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-install-and-use-sqlite-on-ubuntu-20-04

# sqlite3 ecommerce.db

To run the flask app:

- cd path/to/project
- source venv/bin/activate
- python3 app.py
- In a browser open http://127.0.0.1:5000/

The two curly brackets {{ python expression }} means there is a python expression that will be evaluated.

HTTP requests

- a GET request = is when we load a website or retrieve the HTML on a page (retrieve info)
- a POST request = when we make some kind of change to a database or the state of the website (creating or updating something)

To solve the error - TypeError: create_all() got an unexpected keyword argument 'app'
=> check this link
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ym-LtvGhbwQ&ab_channel=PeterSchneider
